content: To those saying you're getting inconsistency results: most people have a mix of face shapes. For example, my face is long, but I also have an angular jaw/chin with high cheek bones. Depending on the photo, I either get diamond or oblong. When I look at my face, I can see why I get both results. Just use the app then look at your face in the mirror. Play around with hair styles, too, that is a key giveaway. For instance, I rock blunt bangs so despite my angular chin, I'm still more oblong than diamond. Use your better judgement.
replyContent: Thank you for sharing your experience and thought about the app and the topic! üëç
